With the start of a new year I always seem to find a little extra motivation to kickstart some healthy habits into motion as part of my regular routine! Three things for me I’m going to incorporate into my daily routine:
1) Drink more water everyday no matter my training load
2) Give myself time at the end of the day to stretch, breathe and decompress 
3) Be a more mindful snacker by choosing nutritious options to help me between meals!
Thanks to the @more_rewards fueling sport program and @saveonfoods I am all set up for success and on the right track! #More Rewards #FuelingSport #SaveOnFoods #FuelTheJourney

Hey!👋🏽 It’s National Girls and Women in Sports Day! Sport/ Soccer has forever changed my life in the most positive of ways! Learned valuable Life lessons + gained Life Long friendships = Grateful ❤️ Hoping to continue to inspire girls to stay in sport through my story &  love for the game! Never forget you belong and you matter! #ngwsd

Hey everyone! As the 2023 prep begins and some questions arise, I wanted to let fans know that I unfortunately am going to be missing the start of the year as I picked up an injury at the end of 2022 and it required surgery! It wasn’t just old age as I had thought haha. I’m currently rehabbing and working hard to get back to join Kansas City & Canada as soon as I can knowing my return will be stronger than ever with the amazing support team I have around me! I’m down but not out and can’t wait to see you all on the pitch when I’m ready! Until then I’ll continue to be the biggest hype woman supporting my teammates to do big things this year!
For players who continue to give their everything, we are simply demanding to be treated as we so rightly deserve. Enough. Is. Enough!

This past week I was very fortunate to get the opportunity to meet the honourable Lieutenant Governor and Premier Stefanson to receive the Order of Manitoba and the Queen’s Jubilee Medal! Honoured and Grateful to be recognized by the Province of Manitoba and my Hometown in this way! I really do love what I do and where I come from and just want to keep inspiring those around me to follow their passion! Thank you to all who continue to believe in me and have supported along the way!

Missing this….🥹

By this time you all have probably heard or seen the news. Heartbroken to know I will not be participating at the World Cup this summer, despite every effort and final push in my rehab process to make it so. I was so hopeful to make it back in time but sometimes the story just doesn’t get written how you’d want it to. 

This team has my heart and are my family and deserve the best version of Desiree Scott. Missing this tournament will be one of the hardest things I’ve had to do but if my rehab process has taught me anything, it’s that I still love this game so much and nothing worth having comes easy. I’ll continue to put in work to get back to being the Destroyer we all know.

I am so grateful for all the support surrounding me  to get me back out on the pitch again soon! Until then I’ll be the biggest hype-woman cheering so freaking loud as this group begins their WC Journey. 

Team - shine bright and go show the world exactly who we are! So much belief in you all! Enjoy every moment of the climb and know all of Canada is behind you!
Love you all so much xo ❤️🇨🇦

Grateful to be able to spend time with this group in the WC Pre-camp in Australia! I got daily reminders of why I love this team so much and why I continue to work so hard to stay a part of it. This team is one of a kind! ❤️ I’m choosing to look at the positives from my time with the team despite my disappointment, knowing the progress I have made and using it to push me forward. One step at a time 👣🇨🇦 ….. until next time ✌🏽heading back to refresh, refocus, rehab some mo’ and of course cheer on my squad! Thank you to everyone who has shown me so much love and support 💕🙌🏽
#CanWNT #TheJourneyContinues

Sincy… we all knew this day would come although I, along with the rest of the world hate that it finally has.

The joy you have brought to my national team experience over the past decade, to have been on the journey with you from Bronze to Gold, to witness the way you inspire me and the rest of the world daily, the way you continue to break barriers, speak your truth and do it all so selflessly to better the sport - How lucky I have been! I am in awe of you @c_sinc12 

Despite all your accolades you remain the most humble human - being the greatest ever - and that is a major reason why I love you! To share the pitch with you has been one of my greatest honours, to hype you up will always be one of my favorite things to do and to look back on all the memories, moments and laughter will be forever treasured! Thank you is not enough.  Cheers to you my girl ❤️👏🏽🇨🇦 🥂

I’m so excited to help share this announcement that the winner of the 2023 @Ally Award is Becky Sauerbrunn! The Ally Award recognizes a player that is a great teammate on and off the field, and as a former teammate of Becky’s, I can’t think of a more deserving person for this award. Congrats, Becky!
